{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsQWKpigL7K2RJuzZ6Hd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The permissions fix resolved the auth errors for both, but `app-client` now hits a separate issue: it tries to declare `app-queue` with only `x-queue-type: classic`, while the queue (created earlier by `app-producer`) also has `x-queue-mode: lazy`. RabbitMQ rejects redeclaration with mismatched arguments. To satisfy \"healthy deployments\" without deleting the queue (which holds 116 messages — avoiding data loss), I'll patch `app-client`'s declare payload to match the existing queue's arguments."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":588,"cache_read_input_tokens":52883,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":588},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"afc25e59-58cb-4815-93ac-c59109c6fcbc","uuid":"8f2171ad-80ab-4e10-9121-284cb823417d","request_id":"req_011CcsQWJoxGNH1PJYfhLw9q"}
